visibility: SANDBOX
license: OFL
category: display
subsets: menu,latin

family: Macondo

designer: John Vargas Beltrán

approved: true
description: <p>Macondo. The first purpose of \
  this typeface was to provide an original and \
  systematized style of calligraphy adapted \
  into a modern digital font. The forms are \
  inspired by some illustrations created for \
  a tarot card game, itself inspired by the \
  work of Colombian literature Nobel prize \
  winning author, Gabriel García Márquez, \
  «Cien Años de Soledad». Early versions of \
  this font were made in 1997, but recently \
  in 2009 it was substantially improved. \
  Macondo includes several cap swashes and \
  other stylish alternates, and a sister family \
  <a href="http://www.google.com/webfonts/specimen/Macondo+Swash+Caps">Macondo Swash Caps</a> \
  is also available.</p>

font.Macondo-Regular.ttf.style: normal
font.Macondo-Regular.ttf.weight: 400

